| `getWorkflowsDir` | `/a/b/c` | `/a/b/c/workflows` |
| `getWorkflowRunDir` | `/a/b/c`, `wf_xxx-yyy` | `/a/b/c/subagents/workflows/wf_xxx-yyy` |
| `getWorkflowSnapshotPath` | `/a/b/c`, `wf_xxx-yyy` | `/a/b/c/workflows/wf_xxx-yyy.json` |
| `getWorkflowJournalPath` | `/a/b/c`, `wf_xxx-yyy` | `/a/b/c/subagents/workflows/wf_xxx-yyy/journal.jsonl` |
| `getWorkflowAgentPath` | `/a/b/c`, `wf_xxx-yyy`, `01234567890abcdef` | journal sibling `agent-01234567890abcdef.jsonl` |
| `isValidWorkflowRunId` accepts | `wf_6f7d9da9-37e` | `true` |
| `isValidWorkflowRunId` rejects short | `wf_short` | `false` |
| `isValidWorkflowRunId` rejects no-prefix | `6f7d9da9-37e` | `false` |
| `isValidWorkflowRunId` rejects uppercase | `wf_6F7D9DA9-37E` | `false` |
| `isValidWorkflowAgentId` accepts | `adca0c33ebe734c2d` (17-hex) | `true` |
| `isValidWorkflowAgentId` rejects 16-hex | 16-char hex | `false` |
| `isValidWorkflowAgentId` rejects 18-hex | 18-char hex | `false` |
| `isValidWorkflowAgentId` rejects non-hex | `XYZ...` | `false` |
| `parseWorkflowSnapshotFilename` valid | `wf_xxx-yyy.json` | `wf_xxx-yyy` |
| `parseWorkflowSnapshotFilename` invalid ext | `wf_xxx-yyy.txt` | `null` |
| `parseWorkflowSnapshotFilename` non-wf | `something.json` | `null` |
| `parseWorkflowAgentFilename` valid | `agent-{17hex}.jsonl` | `{17hex}` |
| `parseWorkflowAgentFilename` invalid prefix | `subagent-{17hex}.jsonl` | `null` |
| `parseWorkflowAgentFilename` invalid id length | `agent-deadbeef.jsonl` | `null` |

### `tests/claude-workflow/journal-parser.test.ts`

| Test | Input line | Expected result |
|------|------------|-----------------|
| Started event with string key/agentId | `{"type":"started","key":"v2:abc","agentId":"adca0c33ebe734c2d"}` | `parsed.workflowEvent === 'started'`, `parsed.workflowAgentId === 'adca0c33ebe734c2d'`, `parsed.type === 'system'`, `parsed.formatted` contains `adca0c3` |
| Result event with string result | `{"type":"result","key":"v2:abc","agentId":"adca...","result":"OK"}` | `parsed.workflowEvent === 'result'`, `parsed.formatted` contains `OK` |
| Result event with object result | `{"type":"result","key":"v2:abc","agentId":"adca...","result":{"foo":"bar"}}` | `parsed.formatted` contains stringified JSON |
| Result with long string → truncation | result string of 200 chars | `parsed.formatted.length` capped under threshold |
| Invalid JSON line | `not-json` | `parse() returns null` (B-T18) |
| Missing `type` | `{"key":"...","agentId":"..."}` | `null` |
| Unknown `type` | `{"type":"foo","key":"...","agentId":"..."}` | `null` |
| Missing `agentId` | `{"type":"started","key":"..."}` | `null` |
| Missing `key` | `{"type":"started","agentId":"..."}` | `null` |
| `agentId` not string (object) | `{"type":"started","key":"v2:x","agentId":{}}` | `null` |
| History-mode timestamp | `new JournalLineParser({ fileMtime: new Date('2026-01-01T00:00:00Z') })` then parse | `parsed.timestamp === '2026-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'` |
| Live-mode after `markLiveMode()` | call `markLiveMode()` then parse | `parsed.timestamp` is current-time ISO (just assert it's a valid ISO ≠ history value) |

### `tests/claude-workflow/snapshot-watcher.test.ts`

Use `mkdtemp` fixtures (per `tests/claude/custom-title.test.ts` convention).

| Test | Setup | Action | Expectation |
|------|-------|--------|-------------|
| Initial read on `start()` | Write `wf_xxx.json` with `status: 'running'` | `await watcher.start()` | `onChange` called once, snapshot.status === 'running' |
| Subsequent write triggers `onChange` after debounce | Started watcher | Write new content; await debounce + 20ms | `onChange` called again, total = 2 |
| Identical content writes deduped | Started watcher | Write same content twice rapidly | `onChange` total = 1 (initial only — re-writing same text is ignored) |
| Invalid JSON content | Started watcher | Write `not json` | `onError` called once, `onChange` NOT called again |
| Recovery after invalid JSON | Continue from above | Write valid JSON | `onChange` called with new snapshot (proves `lastJson` not poisoned by invalid text) |
| `stop()` cancels pending debounce | Started watcher, write file | Call `stop()` immediately before debounce timer fires | `onChange` never called for that write |
| `stop()` is idempotent | Started watcher | Call `stop()` twice | no throw |
| Constructor `debounceMs` honored | Use `debounceMs: 10` | Write file; check timing | `onChange` fires within ~10–50ms (relaxed timing assertion) |

> **Timing trick**: use a small `debounceMs` (e.g. 10) + `setTimeout` waits with generous slack. Avoid raw `Bun.sleep` racing on filesystem flush; use `await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, debounceMs + 30))`.

### `tests/claude-workflow/types.compile.test.ts` (optional, low-cost)

A compile-only assertion file — empty `describe` block plus a few `const _: ParsedLine = { type: '', timestamp: '', raw: null, formatted: '', workflowEvent: 'started' }` lines. Guards against accidental property removal in future refactors. Cheap; skip if it doesn't add clarity.

## Critical Files for Implementation

- `src/claude-workflow/paths.ts` — new; pure helpers, foundation for all subsequent phases
- `src/claude-workflow/types.ts` — new; workflow data structures referenced by detector + watcher in P3+
- `src/claude-workflow/journal-parser.ts` — new; implements `LineParser`, drives journal display in P3
- `src/claude-workflow/snapshot-watcher.ts` — new; only whole-file watcher in codebase, status-line driver in P4/P6
- `src/core/types.ts` — modified; additive optional fields, breaks nothing existing

## Acceptance (P1 internal)

P1 itself has no acceptance criterion in SPEC §16 (passes when "internal tests" green). Concrete green-gate:

1. `bun run typecheck` clean
2. `bun run lint` clean
3. `bun test tests/claude-workflow/` 100% pass (paths + journal-parser + snapshot-watcher)
4. `bun test` (full suite) still green — no regression from `types.ts` additive changes

