# P2: WorkflowSessionFinder + ClaudeSessionFinder Integration + SubagentDetector Exclusion

> Source SPEC: `specs/workflow-support/SPEC.md` §7, §9.4, §16 (Phase 2)
> Acceptance targets: T1, T2, T2b, T3, T3b, T17

## Overview

Phase 2 makes workflow runs **first-class** in agent-tail:

1. New `WorkflowSessionFinder` implements `SessionFinder` for workflow runs (`wf_*.json` snapshots).
2. Existing `ClaudeSessionFinder` is exported (was file-private) and gains two missing methods (`getProjectInfo`, `findLatestInProject`) plus internal workflow integration in `listSessions` + `findBySessionId`.
3. Existing `SubagentDetector.scanForNewSubagents` adds a defensive guard against workflows under `subagents/workflows/`.

After P2, `agent-tail claude --list` shows main sessions **+** workflow runs (path-fuzzy-filtered by `-p`). `agent-tail claude wf_abc...` resolves via the workflow finder. No watcher integration yet — that's P3.

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1 — `src/agents/claude/workflow-agent.ts` (NEW)

```typescript
import { stat } from 'node:fs/promises';
import { homedir } from 'node:os';
import { join } from 'node:path';
import { Glob } from 'bun';
import type { SessionFinder } from '../agent.interface.ts';
import type {
  ProjectInfo,
  SessionFile,
  SessionListItem,
} from '../../core/types.ts';
import {
  isValidWorkflowRunId,
  parseWorkflowSnapshotFilename,
} from '../../claude-workflow/paths.ts';
import type { WorkflowSnapshot } from '../../claude-workflow/types.ts';

export class WorkflowSessionFinder implements SessionFinder {
  private readonly baseDir = join(homedir(), '.claude', 'projects');

  getBaseDir(): string { return this.baseDir; }
  async findLatest(options: { project?: string }): Promise<SessionFile | null>;
  async findBySessionId(
    sessionId: string,
    options: { project?: string }
  ): Promise<SessionFile | null>;
  async getProjectInfo(sessionPath: string): Promise<ProjectInfo | null>;
  async findLatestInProject(projectDir: string): Promise<SessionFile | null>;
  async listSessions(options: {
    project?: string;
    limit?: number;
  }): Promise<SessionListItem[]>;

  /** Shared collection helper (SPEC §7.2). */
  private async _collectWorkflows(options: { project?: string }): Promise<InternalWorkflow[]>;
}

interface InternalWorkflow {
  file: SessionFile;            // path=snapshot path; mtime; agentType='claude'; customTitle='wf:...'
  runId: string;
  sessionUuid: string;
  status?: 'running' | 'completed' | 'failed';
  workflowName?: string;
}
```

#### Behavior contract per method

- **`getBaseDir()`** — `~/.claude/projects`. Used by tests for fixture injection (parallel to `ClaudeSessionFinder` pattern).
- **`_collectWorkflows(options)`** — SPEC §7.2 pseudocode:
  - Scan `${baseDir}` with `Glob('**/workflows/wf_*.json')`.
  - Validate each filename via `parseWorkflowSnapshotFilename`.
  - Fuzzy filter on full path when `options.project` set (lowercase `.includes()` — aligned with `_collectMainSessions`).
  - Extract `sessionUuid` = path segment immediately before `workflows/` segment.
  - Read snapshot file (best-effort JSON.parse) to populate `workflowName` and `status`. Read failures degrade gracefully — entry still listed with `customTitle = 'wf:{runId}'`.
  - Sort by `mtime` descending.
  - Return `InternalWorkflow[]`.
- **`findLatest({ project? })`** — Calls `_collectWorkflows({ project })`, returns first entry's `SessionFile` or null. Aligns with SPEC §7.1: "不傳 `options.project` 時掃所有專案".
- **`findBySessionId(sessionId, { project? })`** — Treat `sessionId` as runId. Resolve precedence: exact runId match > runId prefix match > runId contains. Returns the highest-precedence entry's `SessionFile`. Returns null if no match.
- **`getProjectInfo(sessionPath)`** — `sessionPath` is a workflow `wf_*.json` path. Reverse-derive main session JSONL path via the existing `{enc-cwd}/{UUID}/workflows/wf_*.json` → `{enc-cwd}/{UUID}.jsonl` rule, then delegate to `ClaudeSessionFinder.getProjectInfo(mainPath)` (added in Step 2). Returns null if main session unresolvable. **Implementation note**: we don't directly couple to `ClaudeSessionFinder` in `WorkflowSessionFinder` — that creates a tight cycle. Instead we use the same `readCwdFromHead` helper directly on the derived main session path.
- **`findLatestInProject(projectDir)`** — `projectDir` is the encoded form (`-Users-...`). Calls `_collectWorkflows({ project: projectDir })`, returns first or null.
- **`listSessions({ project?, limit? })`** — Maps `_collectWorkflows` results to `SessionListItem`s with workflow-flag fields populated; honors limit (default 20).

#### `SessionListItem` shape per SPEC §7.2 R4-S2

```typescript
{
  // SessionFile fields:
  path: '/Users/.../wf_xxxx.json',
  mtime: <Date>,
  agentType: 'claude',
  customTitle: 'wf:briefshare-impl',           // fallback 'wf:{runId}'

  // SessionListItem additions:
  shortId: 'wf_xxxxxxxx-xxx',                  // runId itself
  project: '-Users-x-code-foo',                // encoded project dir name (parent of {UUID})

  // Workflow extensions (new in P1):
  logType: 'workflow',
  workflowRunId: 'wf_xxxxxxxx-xxx',
  workflowSessionUuid: '<UUID>',
  workflowStatus: 'running' | 'completed' | 'failed',
}
```

### Step 2 — `src/agents/claude/claude-agent.ts` modifications

#### 2.1 Export `ClaudeSessionFinder`

```typescript
- class ClaudeSessionFinder implements SessionFinder {
+ export class ClaudeSessionFinder implements SessionFinder {
```

(Line 33.)

#### 2.2 Add `getProjectInfo(sessionPath)`

Place after `listSessions` (around line 144). Implementation:

```typescript
async getProjectInfo(sessionPath: string): Promise<ProjectInfo | null> {
  // sessionPath: ~/.claude/projects/{encoded-dir}/{UUID}.jsonl
  // Decode {encoded-dir} → cwd via reverse mapping ('-' → '/')
  const parts = sessionPath.split('/');
  const projectsIdx = parts.indexOf('projects');
  if (projectsIdx < 0 || projectsIdx + 1 >= parts.length) return null;
  const encodedDir = parts[projectsIdx + 1]!;
  const projectDir = encodedDir;  // pass-through; auto-switch uses encoded form

  // displayName: read cwd from session head (existing helper)
  const cwd = await readCwdFromHead(sessionPath);
  return {
    projectDir,
    ...(cwd ? { displayName: cwd } : {}),
  };
}
```

#### 2.3 Add `findLatestInProject(projectDir)`

```typescript
async findLatestInProject(projectDir: string): Promise<SessionFile | null> {
  return this.findLatest({ project: projectDir });
}
```

Simple delegation — the existing `findLatest` already filters by `project` (fuzzy match). Auto-switch wires `findLatestInProject` so we just need the method present on the interface.

#### 2.4 Internal workflow finder + listSessions merge

Add private `_workflowFinder` field (lazy init in constructor) — avoid module-level singleton.

```typescript
import { WorkflowSessionFinder } from './workflow-agent.ts';

export class ClaudeSessionFinder implements SessionFinder {
  private baseDir: string;
  private readonly _workflowFinder: WorkflowSessionFinder;

  constructor() {
    this.baseDir = join(homedir(), '.claude', 'projects');
    this._workflowFinder = new WorkflowSessionFinder();
  }

  // ...

  async listSessions(options: {
    project?: string;
    limit?: number;
  }): Promise<SessionListItem[]> {
    const limit = options.limit ?? 20;

    // 1. Existing: main sessions (with tail enrichment).
    //    Note: existing code does slice(0, limit) BEFORE enrich. We change order:
    //    collect all main → also collect workflows → merge → slice → enrich main only.
    const mainItems = await this._collectMainSessions({ project: options.project });
    const wfItems = await this._workflowFinder.listSessions({ project: options.project });

    // 2. Merge & sort by lastActivityTime ?? mtime (workflow snapshots only have mtime).
    const merged: SessionListItem[] = [...mainItems, ...wfItems].sort((a, b) => {
      const ta = (a.lastActivityTime ?? a.mtime).getTime();
      const tb = (b.lastActivityTime ?? b.mtime).getTime();
      return tb - ta;
    });
    const sliced = merged.slice(0, limit);

    // 3. Enrich only main session items (workflow already has snapshot metadata).
    await Promise.all(
      sliced.map(async (item) => {
        if (item.logType === 'workflow') return;        // skip
        const [lastTs, title, cwd] = await Promise.all([
          readLastTimestampFromJSONL(item.path),
          readCustomTitleFromTail(item.path),
          readCwdFromHead(item.path),
        ]);
        item.lastActivityTime = lastTs ?? undefined;
        if (title) item.customTitle = title;
        if (cwd) item.project = cwd;
      })
    );

    // 4. Re-sort after enrichment (timestamps may have moved).
    sliced.sort((a, b) => {
      const ta = (a.lastActivityTime ?? a.mtime).getTime();
      const tb = (b.lastActivityTime ?? b.mtime).getTime();
      return tb - ta;
    });

    return sliced;
  }
}
```

