|------|-------|--------|----------|
| `start()` on non-existent dir doesn't throw | no `workflows/` dir | `await detector.start()` | resolves; outputHandler.debug called |
| New `wf_*.json` file in workflows/ triggers onNewWorkflow | `workflows/` dir exists | start, then `writeFile(wf_xxxxxxxx-abc.json)` | `onNewWorkflow` called within ~200ms with matching runId/snapshotPath/transcriptDir |
| Duplicate runId from rapid filesystem events deduped | path B fires twice for same file | start + 2 rapid writes | `onNewWorkflow` called exactly once |
| Filename not matching wf_ pattern ignored | `workflows/not-a-wf.json` written | dir watch fires | `onNewWorkflow` not called |
| `prefillKnown(runId)` suppresses dir-watch emission | prefill then create file with that runId | start + writeFile | `onNewWorkflow` not called |
| `stop()` is idempotent | start, stop, stop | no throw |
| onNewWorkflow throwing → runId rolled back, retried | onNewWorkflow rejects first call, succeeds 2nd | trigger file write | onNewWorkflow called twice, eventually succeeds |

### `tests/claude-workflow/workflow-attachment.test.ts` (NEW)

